<br>
I pulled some Warden guy in the basement of SSRA. Even con at 60.<br>
<br>
A level 52 SK was in the group, with notably lower HPs than the epic. Epic pet got OWNED by this mob. His average hit was in the neighborhood of 31 by looks. The SK steps in and is able to take the beating with less HPs adding close to 40 secs between needing CHs over the pet.<br>
<br>
I don't know what your experiences are, but at 65 I'd like to believe my pet is better at tanking than a level 52 Knight class. He sure isn't snaring, LoH, buffing, debuffing, Healing or HTing.<br>
<br>
Why have a mage along on a raid, when you could have a melee class instead? Unless pets are once again viable on raids. This is a solid question. Melees outtank the pets by a HUGE margin, Wizards out nuke us by HUGE margins. I don't mind either one, and would never want to tread on their turf. But, I want the 2 to add up. <br>
<br>
The epic quest isnt that hard now. On my server crowns are selling for 120K. Hate staff MQ has been offered for 40K. It took me 30 or so trips to PoH when I did it, at the time there were only about 10 guilds with the relative power to do it.<br>
<br>
The reason a lot of you newer folks are having so much trouble in PoH is that all the casual gamers are getting levels finally and exploring the old content. Look at my crappy drawing here.<br>
<br>
Ding             .<br>
LVL             .. ..<br>
60            ...    ...<br>
!!         ....         ....<br>
      .....                 .....<br>
 ......                          .......<br>
            TIME<br>
<br>
As time goes on, more and more people reach high end content. I was near the start of this on time. We are now just beyond the peak of that chart. More people dinged 60 in the past 3 months than any time before. Those people all need something to do now. The easiest stuff happens to be the old world and Kunark, so thats where they head. Mobs such as Trak/VS/Phinny/Lodizal/Kelorek Dar/And PoH, PoF minis rarely live to see a sunset. These mobs do not require the well equipped droves of level 60s that SSRA and VT require. (Yes, I know lodizal and Kelorek Dar arent in kunark, but they are of the same difficulty)<br>
<br>
The other problem you have is justifying going to PoA to get crowns. The loot that quests out of there for melees is pretty crappy in comparison to what they have now. The 41% haste belts are about the only exception. <br>
<br>
When I did my PoA raid for my crown, we got tons of upgrades for people in our guild, and people were excited to do it. Those days are past. <br>
<br>
Either join a guild that is just now entering Kunark and Old world content, or buy it from one. Those guilds now dominate the old world and the old planes, and rightfully so, I say. <p><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD>
